  "body": "How am I suppose to flex on people if EthStats isn't supported? ðŸ˜† \r\n\r\nAs far as I can tell there doesn't appear to be support for EthStats? Attempting to use the --ethstats flag results in this:\r\n\r\n```\r\npanic: runtime error: invalid memory address or nil pointer dereference\r\n[signal SIGSEGV: segmentation violation code=0x1 addr=0x0 pc=0x101667e]\r\n\r\ngoroutine 214 [running]:\r\ngithub.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/ethstats.(*Service).loop(0xc000252cc0)\r\n        github.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth@/ethstats/ethstats.go:147 +0x15e\r\ncreated by github.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth/ethstats.(*Service).Start\r\n        github.com/ledgerwatch/turbo-geth@/ethstats/ethstats.go:118 +0x5a\r\n```\r\n\r\nAlso, I could be mistaken but I don't THINK `tg` or `rpcdaemon` have the necessary API endpoints required to run the standalone ethstats client?",
